The article discusses the upcoming 20th anniversary of the September 11 terrorist attacks and emphasizes the enduring pain felt by the families and loved ones of the victims. It acknowledges the personal devastation experienced by these individuals and highlights the long-lasting effects, such as children growing up without parents and spouses navigating life without their partners. The author, who understands the grief of losing someone suddenly, expresses empathy for the families and recognizes their pursuit of accountability and justice for the past 20 years. They promise transparency and adherence to guidance on state secrets privilege. The author also expresses condolences and a commitment to engage respectfully with the 9/11 families as they move forward.